<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1678,1993]" pageId="7" pageNumber="350">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,450,1714,1741]" pageId="7" pageNumber="350">Original description:</emphasis>
“con apice più elevato e reticolatura meno marcata” [with a more prominent apex and a less marked reticulate sculpture—with respect to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Linnaeus, 1758)" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[710,1093,1750,1777]" class="Gastropoda" family="Fissurellidae" genus="Diodora" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepetellida" pageId="7" pageNumber="350" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="graeca">
<emphasis box="[710,891,1750,1776]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="350">Diodora graeca</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Linnaeus, C." box="[906,1084,1750,1777]" pageId="7" pageNumber="350" refId="ref17590" refString="Linnaeus, C. (1758) Systema naturae per regna tria naturae, secundum classes, ordines, genera, species, cum characteribus, differentiis, synonymis, locis. Tomus I. Laurentii Salvii, Holmiae, 824 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 542" type="book" year="1758">Linnaeus, 1758</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, reported as 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[1238,1436,1750,1776]" class="Gastropoda" family="Fissurellidae" genus="Fissurella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepetellida" pageId="7" pageNumber="350" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="graeca">
<emphasis box="[1238,1436,1750,1776]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="350">Fissurella graeca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L.].
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="350" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1678,1993]" pageId="7" pageNumber="350">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,317,1823,1849]" pageId="7" pageNumber="350">Remarks:</emphasis>
having been instituted as a geographic race, we rank it subspecific, and thus available (
<bibRefCitation author="ICZN &amp; International Commission on Zoological Nomenclature" box="[1298,1432,1823,1849]" pageId="7" pageNumber="350" refId="ref17437" refString="ICZN [International Commission on Zoological Nomenclature] (2012) International code of zoological nomenclature. 4 th Edition. International Trust for Zoological Nomenclature, London. Available from: http: // www. iczn. org / (accessed 15 Feburary 2019)" type="url" year="2012">ICZN 2012</bibRefCitation>
: Art. 10, glossary). Considered a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Linnaeus, 1758)" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[739,1121,1858,1885]" class="Gastropoda" family="Fissurellidae" genus="Diodora" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepetellida" pageId="7" pageNumber="350" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="graeca">
<emphasis box="[739,920,1858,1884]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="350">Diodora graeca</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Linnaeus, C." box="[936,1113,1858,1885]" pageId="7" pageNumber="350" refId="ref17590" refString="Linnaeus, C. (1758) Systema naturae per regna tria naturae, secundum classes, ordines, genera, species, cum characteribus, differentiis, synonymis, locis. Tomus I. Laurentii Salvii, Holmiae, 824 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 542" type="book" year="1758">Linnaeus, 1758</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Fasulo, G." box="[1165,1326,1858,1885]" pageId="7" pageNumber="350" pagination="29 - 32" refId="ref16988" refString="Fasulo, G. (2012) Taxa di molluschi marini &quot; napoletani &quot; per toponimia. Notiziario S. I. M., 30 (2), 29 - 32." type="journal article" year="2012">Fasulo (2012)</bibRefCitation>
, although no figures were ever published by 
<bibRefCitation author="Bellini, R." box="[533,705,1894,1921]" pageId="7" pageNumber="350" pagination="1 - 87" refId="ref15827" refString="Bellini, R. (1929 a) I molluschi del Golfo di Napoli (studi precedenti, l'ambiente, enumerazione e sinonimia). Annuario del Museo Zoologico della R. Universita di Napoli, 6 (2), 1 - 87." type="journal article" year="1929">Bellini (1929a)</bibRefCitation>
. The original description may easily fit several Mediterranean fissurellid limpets, all occurring in Capri Island and not even congeneric—e.g. 
<taxonomicName authority="(Linnaeus, 1758)" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[1009,1431,1930,1957]" class="Gastropoda" family="Fissurellidae" genus="Fissurella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepetellida" pageId="7" pageNumber="350" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="nubecula">
<emphasis box="[1009,1231,1930,1956]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="350">Fissurella nubecula</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Linnaeus, C." box="[1246,1423,1930,1957]" pageId="7" pageNumber="350" refId="ref17590" refString="Linnaeus, C. (1758) Systema naturae per regna tria naturae, secundum classes, ordines, genera, species, cum characteribus, differentiis, synonymis, locis. Tomus I. Laurentii Salvii, Holmiae, 824 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 542" type="book" year="1758">Linnaeus, 1758</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[151,263,1967,1992]" class="Gastropoda" family="Fissurellidae" genus="Diodora" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepetellida" pageId="7" pageNumber="350" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="graeca">
<emphasis box="[151,263,1967,1992]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="350">D. graeca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Defrance, 1820)" authorityName="Defrance" authorityYear="1820" baseAuthorityName="Defrance" baseAuthorityYear="1820" box="[277,652,1966,1993]" class="Gastropoda" family="Fissurellidae" genus="Diodora" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepetellida" pageId="7" pageNumber="350" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="italica">
<emphasis box="[277,451,1966,1992]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="350">Diodora italica</emphasis>
(Defrance, 1820)
</taxonomicName>
. Thus, it is considered a 
<emphasis box="[928,1094,1966,1992]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="350">nomen dubium</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="ICZN &amp; International Commission on Zoological Nomenclature" box="[1108,1243,1967,1993]" pageId="7" pageNumber="350" refId="ref17437" refString="ICZN [International Commission on Zoological Nomenclature] (2012) International code of zoological nomenclature. 4 th Edition. International Trust for Zoological Nomenclature, London. Available from: http: // www. iczn. org / (accessed 15 Feburary 2019)" type="url" year="2012">ICZN 2012</bibRefCitation>
: glossary).
</paragraph>
